INTRODUCTION
------------

Form Element States module provides a field widget for all core
field types to add state properties into it. Common use cases is
some fields need to be visible/hide/required depends on other
field value.

* For a full description of the module visit
  https://www.drupal.org/project/form_element_states

* To submit bug reports and feature suggestions, or to track changes visit
  https://www.drupal.org/project/issues/form_element_states


REQUIREMENTS
------------

This module requires field module from Drupal core.


INSTALLATION
------------

Install the Form Element States module as you would normally install a
contributed Drupal module. Visit https://www.drupal.org/node/1897420 for further
information.


CONFIGURATION
-------------

1. Navigate to Administration > Structure > Content Types
2. Go to manage form display to any content type.
3. Select widget from select list(eg:textfield with states) from field row.
4. Add states property in the textarea(State properties)
5  Add each state property in new line.

Example :- visible|field_toogle|checked|TRUE
Where:
visible - state action
field_toogle - field name
checked - condition
TRUE - Condition value

For more help how states are in drupal Form element

https://api.drupal.org/api/drupal/core!includes!common.inc/function/drupal_process_states

